article_title: Gold Prices Slip From Three-Week High
article_text:
Gold prices slipped from a three-week high on Monday as investors weighed the likely path of global monetary policy.

The most actively traded contract, for December delivery, fell $2, or 0.2%, to settle at $1,195.70 a troy ounce on the Comex division of the New York Mercantile Exchange.
